                           </entry>
                        </row>
                     </tbody>
                  </tgroup>
               </table>The second line indicates the state of the isolated system: <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Standby</uicontrol>, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Normal Operation</uicontrol>, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Battery Operation</uicontrol>, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Static Bypass Operation</uicontrol>. Input voltage, output voltage, and output frequency are not shown
in maintenance bypass operation.</p>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Main Menu and Navigation</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">From
the main menu it is possible to configure and monitor the system through
the submenus: <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">System Status</uicontrol>, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">System
Control</uicontrol>, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Event Logging</uicontrol>, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Settings</uicontrol>, <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Diagnosis</uicontrol>, and <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Configuration</uicontrol>. Use the UP/ DOWN and the ENTER display
navigation keys to navigate through the menus. Press the ESC key to
return to a previous menu. Press the HELP key to access help information
about a menu point.</p>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
